Rule Learning, Probabilistic Methods. 

Rule Learning is present in the text as the paper discusses the use of an AQ-type learning algorithm to search for the best hypothesis in a given representation space. 

Probabilistic Methods are also present in the text as the paper discusses the use of data-driven constructive induction (DCI) to search for a better representation space by analyzing input examples (data). DCI uses two classes of representation space improvement operators: constructors and destructors, which are probabilistic in nature.
